supports HTML5 video The infrastructure works for project Al Bareh in Diyar Al Muharraq, the implementation of which began in November last year, have been completed. The works included power and water connections, and telecommunication systems installation. Moreover, the scope of work included the installation of irrigation and sewage systems as well as road lighting and paving works. The Diyar Al Muharraq development company carried out the works. On the other hand, the project’s leading consulting was Aecom. The firm supervised and oversaw its planning alongside Jahecon. The Al Bareh in Diyar Al Muharraq possesses a spacious nature. It overlooks the spectacular views of the city’s main water canal as well as the Gulf. Moreover, it features an inner road network. This road network further links to key destinations as well as locations within the city. Also Read: Marassi Terraces, a Part of Marassi Al Bahrain Project Launched Al Bareh is located within the northwest region of DIyar Al Muharraq. In the country, Diyar Al Muharraq is one of the largest cities with integration. The region offers a variety of housing solutions as well as a luxurious modern lifestyle. For all nationalities, the project offers exceptional residential opportunities. This includes the project’s availability on a freehold basis. Ahmed Ali Al Ammadi, the CEO Engineer commented on the project. Upon confirming its official completion he gave assurance that the project aimed to maintain the highest of standards. Ahmed Ali pointed out that meeting the needs of residents and citizens in the country will always be a priority. Thus, he revealed that the firm aims to introduce and build more residential projects in Bahrain.